@AstroPjs Considering that Hong Kong is where I grew up and where most of my family live, I don’t think of this as falling into that trope. In fact I was trying to bring some nuance into the very binary country comparisons that have happened through the pandemic

@katheri26872038 I hear you. It's paradoxical, but I felt more freedom and less Covid anxiety in a city with no cases thanks to all the restrictions! But, as I wrote, I don't think there's a one size fits all answer and vaccines and meds are changing the picture.

@NesseKy It's a totally personal decision - both b/c everyone's risk tolerance is different and b/c local circumstances (everything from case rates to covid prevention policies) differ. I'd start w/ the question: is your goal zero infection? Are you ok with potential infection?
